Download the file Auth.zip from  https://aka.ms/authscripts
Unzip the files to a folder such as c:\temp .
From an elevated PowerShell session (admin), change into the folder where scripts are saved and run .\start-auth.ps1 -vAuth -accepteula
switch user and try to signin the impacted user account with WHFB PIN to reproduce the issue.
when issue reproduced, take a screenshot of the error. then switch back to orignal admin account, From the elevated PowerShell session, run .\stop-auth.ps1
